captions.text:
- Having dealt extensively
with children and adults,

I can say that a drunken
adult and a five-year-old
are exactly the same thing.
(child singing)
- I fell asleep in my hiding spot
while playing hide and seek.
I was drunk.

Woke up about 6 o'clock in
the morning the next day

not really understanding
what had happened that night.
- I knocked out a guy's tooth

for telling the same stupid
joke over and over again.
I was a kid.
Sorry, Chris.

- I slept over at one
of my friend's houses
and peed his bed two nights in a row.
I was drunk.

We had to hide it from
'em both times because

we didn't want them to like,
kick me out of the house.

- Someone told a knock-knock
joke and I heard it,
and I cried for four hours straight.
I was... drunk.

I don't remember what
the knock-knock joke was.

That's where I learned
that comedy is pain.

- I was at a party and
I wound up getting naked
and throwing a bag of shit at everyone.
I was a kid.
My parents were having a Christmas party.

I appeared at the top of
the stairs completely naked
and with a bag in my hand,
and before they could say or do anything,
I threw it at the wall

and it turned out to
be a very full diaper.
Merry Christmas.
- I got in the driver's seat of a Jaguar
and immediately crashed it into a tree.
I was a kid
and my mom was much more careful with me
in the car from then on.
- I saw a single boob in a ball pit.
And I was drunk.

It was with this girl that
was like a friend of a friend

and I was having a terrible
time reading her advances.

We ended up in a ball pit
that my friends and I had
in their dorm room.

We decided to make a ball pit;
that's a whole 'nother story.

Honestly, only seeing
one boob of this girl
really made sense if you knew this girl.
- I slapped a stranger in the face
because he didn't wish me happy birthday.
I was drunk.
Started chasing after me
and I hide in a Whole Foods parking garage
while my friends talked him down.

Drunk-me thought this was the
funniest thing in the world.

- I had to go pee on
a really long car ride

and then when I was almost
home, I peed on the elevator.
I was drunk.
I'd never, no one ever knew.

It was just, it was a
long night (laughing).
♫ la la la
♫ la la la
♫ la la la la la la la ♫
- You know, I'm like, it's my birthday.
And he goes back, "It doesn't matter.
"Everyone's got a birthday."
(slap)
